oc:kn_2c7aa3e2 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing a hook system that needs defense-in-depth" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Combine multiple hook patterns across PreToolUse, Stop, and SessionStart event types for comprehensive multi-layered protection." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-hook protection leaves gaps; layering security validation, test enforcement, and build verification provides robust coverage." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_6a25b7d7 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring PreToolUse hooks with matchers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use overly broad matchers like 'Bash' without specific prompt validation logic, as this can block legitimate operations and degrade user experience." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Broad matchers without nuanced validation create false positives that frustrate users and reduce trust in the hook system." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_82f802a0 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When hooks are expensive or only needed in certain project contexts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use flag files (e.g., .enable-security-scan) to make hooks conditionally active, allowing opt-in for performance-intensive or project-specific checks." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Flag files let teams enable/disable hooks without modifying plugin code, supporting temporary debugging and feature-flag workflows." .

oc:kn_a6cf1b3f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using flag-file-based conditional hooks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Claude Code must be restarted after creating or removing flag files for hooks to recognize the changes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Flag file existence is checked at hook registration time, not at runtime, so changes require a session restart to take effect." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e3b51b2b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When hooks need user-configurable or per-project settings" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use JSON configuration files (e.g., .claude/my-plugin.local.json) to drive hook behavior such as strict mode, file size limits, and allowed paths." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Configuration-driven hooks decouple validation rules from hook code, enabling team-specific rules and dynamic criteria without code changes." .

